{
  "texts": [
    "We run our synthetic-data-generation process on a large number of parallel CPU workers, each seeded with a different random seed to reduce duplications.",
    "After running this process on 100,000 CPU workers for 72 h, we obtained roughly 500 million synthetic proof examples.",
    "We reformat the proof statements to their canonical form (for example, sorting arguments of individual terms and sorting terms within the same proof step, etc.)",
    "to avoid shallow deduplication against itself and against the test set.",
    "At the end, we obtain 100 million unique theorem-proof examples."
  ]
}